Preparing for concerts, individual vocal training, basics of vocal techniques, performing publicly, participating in different music projects with orchestras, leading soloists etc., participating in events connected to the University of Tartu.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To enable students of the University of Tartu to participate in women's choir practice.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successfully completing the course students: - have the necessary knowledge, skills and experience in singing in a female choir; - are familiar with elementary music theory and have basic knowledge about music; - have acquired essential knowledge about the basics of vocal techniques; fit in the choir, listen the tuning and consider the rest of the chor while singing; - have learnt the choir's repertoire for the respective year.
